[{"id":"VR817518","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div><div class=\"stimulus_reference\"><div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows a horizontal wire, carrying a current I to the right, and two points below the wire. Point P is a distance r sub 0 below the wire. Point Q is to the right of point P and is a distance 2 r sub 0 below the wire.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR817518.g01.svg\"/></div></div></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">A wire carries a current <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"I\"><math alttext=\"I\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>I</mi></math></span></span> to the right. Point <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"P\"><math alttext=\"P\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi></math></span></span> is at a distance <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"r sub 0 \"><math alttext=\"r sub 0 \" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>r</mi><mn>0</mn></msub></math></span></span> below the wire and Point <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"Q \"><math alttext=\"Q \" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Q</mi></math></span></span> is at a distance <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2 r sub 0\"><math alttext=\"2 r sub 0\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn><msub><mi>r</mi><mn>0</mn></msub></math></span></span> below the wire, as shown. Which of the following is equal to the ratio of the magnitude of the magnetic field <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"B sub P\"><math alttext=\"B sub P\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>B</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi></msub></math></span></span> at Point <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"P \"><math alttext=\"P \" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi></math></span></span> to the magnitude of the magnetic field <span class=\"math_ex